cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper discusses the specification of complex structures in distributed service function chaining, which involves networking, distributed computing, and software engineering concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of distributed cloud centers, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper presents a context-free grammar for abstract description, which is related to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of YANG data modeling language, which is related to the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper presents examples of using the models for complex services, which is related to the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
